blogs.title: guest 1st
blogs.content: I became aware of the fact I was on a moped at 35 mph going downhill when I crossed over the trolley tracks. My back tire got caught in the indented groove of the tracks. My moped slid along the pavement;
blogs.author: guest

blogs.title: 4th Blog Revised
blogs.content: I made it home, I left the moped in the driveway. My parents weren’t home since it was Thursday, and they were at the bar. I went to a mirror in the bathroom to inspect myself.
blogs.author: aditya

blogs.title: guest 2nd rev
blogs.content: I was relieved. My chin was there, only crimson. I must’ve left a pretty good size chunk of flesh on the street. But most importantly my chin was there to take another fall.
blogs.author: guest
